# i18n Bilingual (es-MX / en)

- All user-facing strings via `next-intl`; keys in `messages/es-MX.json` and `messages/en.json`.
- Default locale: **es-MX**; English for expats and MLB import catalog pages.
- Never concatenate translated fragments; use ICU placeholders.

```tsx
// BAD
<p>{t('price')}: ${product.price}</p>

// GOOD
<p>{t('product.price', { amount: formatMxn(product.priceMxn) })}</p>
```

- Format dates with `Intl.DateTimeFormat('es-MX')`; phones as +52; addresses use CP/estado/colonia labels.
- Keep key parity: add both locales in the same PR; run i18n-reviewer for tone (Mexico Spanish, not Spain).
